TaxRateRequest - Class in com.ansi.scilla.web.request
Used to request data from the TaxRate table

To get a list of all taxRates:

Request object is not used (GET /taxRate/list)
A TaxRateListResponse is returned

To get a particluar tax Rate:
Request object is not used (GET /taxRate/<taxRateId>)
A TaxRateListResponse is returned

To add a new tax Rate:
POST /taxRate/add with POSTED json string like:
{"location":"Webthing HQ","rate":123.45,"taxAmount":0.03,"effectiveDate":"12/01/2016"}
A TaxRateResponse is returned

To upate an existing tax Rate:
POST /taxRate/<taxRateId> with POSTED json string like:
{"taxRateId":123,"location":"Webthing HQ","rate":123.45,"taxAmount":0.03,"effectiveDate":"12/01/2016"}
A TaxRateResponse is returned

TaxRateServlet - Class in com.ansi.scilla.web.servlets
The url for delete will be of the form /taxRate/ The url for get will be one of: /taxRate/list (retrieves everything) /taxRate/ (retrieves a single record) For 2.0 probably adding state, county and city fields to taxRate table /taxRate/ (Retrieves state contains ) /taxRate// (Retrieves and county contains ) /taxRate///(Retrieves and city contains ) The url for adding a new record will be a POST to: /taxRate/add with parameters in the JSON The url for update will be a POST to: /taxRate/ with parameters in the JSON
